04/05/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- The EU Council of Foreign Ministers started a two-day informal meeting Friday (2 May) on the Greek island of Rhodes.
The meeting was to focus primarily on the Middle East and the reconstruction of Iraq.
On Saturday meanwhile, EU foreign ministers gathered in the town of Kas, in southern Turkey to discuss EU enlargement and post-war Iraq.
Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul noted it was the first meeting of the ministers on non-EU territory.
(Kathimerini, Anadolu, BBC - 03/05/03;
ANA - 02/05/03)
